          "correctOptionId": "opt-C",
          "explanation": "Two unique properties of liquids are surface tension and viscosity. Surface tension is a force that pulls particles at the exposed surface of a liquid toward other liquid particles. Surface tension explains why water forms droplets, like the water droplet that has formed on the leaky faucet pictured in the Figure below . You can learn more about surface tension at this URL: http://io9. com/5668221/an-experiment-with-soap-water-pepper-and-surface-tension ."
